about: Michael has one underlining goal that drives Strategic Marketing Systems- to make his clients more money with little to no work on their part. He has owned 6 different businesses in the food-service industry starting each from scratch and then growing them into multi-million dollar businesses, employing hundreds of people at a time. He built his catering company into one of the top grossing catering firms in the country which was started in his grandmother’s basement. Because of his success in the food-service industry, specifically the catering field, people began to seek Michael out for advice on how to start, build and market catering divisions for their restaurants. This lead to Michael speaking at many seminars around the country on how to successfully market a catering business. Michael then started a consulting firm to help restaurant and catering owners to grow their business. After consulting with several hundred restaurants and caterers Michael developed a Done For You Marketing service for clients. He then expanded into several other niches helping clients in the retail, automotive repair, and chiropractic and healthcare industries to increase sales all with no work on his client’s part. He consistently makes his clients more sales and more money in their pockets each and every month with little to no work on their part in any economy.

about: I am an executive recruiting manager with Robert Half, the world's first and largest specialized financial recruitment service. With over 10 years of experience in leadership, sales, and customer service roles, I have developed a strong set of competencies that enable me to connect talented individuals with rewarding career opportunities. My core competencies include customer relationship management, communication, marketing, project management, and team building. I leverage these skills to build personal relationships with candidates and clients, understand their needs and goals, and match them with the best job opportunities in the finance and accounting sector. I also provide guidance and support to help them navigate their careers and achieve their goals. In addition to my passion for connecting people with the right job opportunities, I am also dedicated to creating positive culture shifts and driving success for Robert Half and its partners. I have a proven track record of executing effective marketing campaigns, managing large projects, improving operational metrics, and mentoring team members to advance their careers. I hold a master's degree in public relations and image management. I am always looking to connect with like-minded professionals who share my passion for helping others and making a positive impact in the world. If you are interested in connecting and exploring ways we can support each other in our careers, I would love to connect with you on LinkedIn.

about: Hi, my name is Victoria Surber. I am graduating in December with my degree in biochemistry from the University of Maryland. I have a strong interest in preforming scientific research. I have centered my coursework around being in a laboratory setting and learning about different methods of research. I have a wide knowledge of different types of instrumentation, procedures, and skills that will aide me in a professional laboratory setting. I chose to enhance my understanding of scientific methods to prepare myself for hands on experience outside of the classroom. I have completed numerous experiments and written full scientific research reports. I also have experience outside of an academic setting in a managerial position. This position enhanced my organizational and problem-solving skills both of which are important and easily transferrable to a position in science. I am ready to continue to build my skills and grow with a company that appreciates curiosity and wanting to learn.

Not only with the job experience that I have gained in my tenure here, but the way we have been able to help our clients and associates in their time of need. My goal is to utilize the knowledge and skills I have obtained in recent years to advance my career as a leader while helping people and changing lives one day at a time. I am a wife, mother of one and have ten wonderful pets. I have a Studio Art degree and love being able to utilize those skills in my everyday life.

about: Manage all aspects of the Williams Sonoma conversion from legacy systems to Oracle Procure to Pay. Ensure all testing and implementation steps were completed and functioning as expected. Spearhead the conversion from Coupa (legacy system) to the Oracle Procurement Module. Ensure smooth transition for uploads from vendors transitioning to a new FBDI spreadsheet for Oracle. Track and ensure all Procurement steps are completed for conversion as well as perform the tasks assigned to Procurement. Manage the OCR (Optical Character Recognition) module implementation. Provide training for field and corporate Procurement users. Assist the AP team with roll out ensuring all testing was completed for invoicing and PO matching.  Hired in June of 2019 by Williams Sonoma Inc. (WSI) (through Robert Half) to help get the Procurement team on track with the conversion from Coupa to Oracle P2P.  After working with implementation team was able to make Procurement the first department fully ready to implement and transition to Oracle.  When the project was pushed to 2020, I was asked to extend my contract and assist both the Procurement and the Accounts Payable departments.  Duties include – o Project management o Training o Implementation Developing training materials and process guides o Managing the parallel testing effort for both Procurement and Accounts Payable o Performing data validations and reconciliations of data and reports, o Testing and trouble-shooting systems  After Oracle Implementation Continued support for all aspects of Procurement Oracle processing, updates, trouble shooting, Issue resolution, support, reporting, data analysis, new release management, etc.  Main support contact for all Invoice/PO matching issues to ensure full resolution.  Was assigned to assist with a data analysis project for one of the Williams Sonoma subsidiaries developing extensive costing models and analysis (Sutter Street)  Responsible for managing punch out and catalog vendors, maintenance, set up, troubleshooting as well as managing the Oracle Business Network functions.  Procurement management for all functions to include o Manage/Create Procurement Agents o Monitor Transaction Console activities for purchase orders and requisitions o Utilize the Collaboration Messaging function for B2B invoice trouble shooting o Utilize the Payables view only function for invoice to PO matching issue resolution o Manage Supplier Content Map Set o All Oracle Procurement management functions

about: As a Client Solutions Manager / Account Executive for Robert Half, I provide highly skilled IT professionals to help companies run effectively and efficiently. I work hard to understand and address the dynamic technology and digital challenges of my clients, and to place the candidates that will help them meet their business goals. I have a strong background in talent acquisition, executive recruiting, business development, and account management, with multiple certifications in diversity and inclusion, communication, and strategic human resources. I also have a passion for communication and customer service, which I apply in my role as a Server/Bartender at Gobbie's Sports Pub & Eatery. I enjoy creating high-quality content that fits the unique needs and objectives of my customers and building lasting relationships with them. I have a profound history of knowledge in B2B, B2C, enterprise and direct sales, strategic social media marketing, corporate and employee benefits, benefit-subrogation, and analytical problem solving. I am a firm believer in adaptation, motivation, and equality for all, and a distinguished witticism and tomfoolery.

about: • • • Accounting & Operations Pro | Process Improvement Enthusiast | Loving Dad • • • I'm a versatile accounting and operations professional with 9+ years of experience driving financial success and operational efficiency across diverse industries. My passion lies in process improvement, strategic planning, and team building, enabling me to excel in fast-paced, high-volume environments. With a strong background in internal financial reporting and collaboration with senior leadership, I effectively prioritize time-sensitive issues and deliver impactful results. As an analytical thinker, I specialize in evaluating operations and implementing improvements. Throughout my career, I have held various positions such as Controller, Fiscal Project Manager, and Corporate Accountant. These roles have honed my skills in managing day-to-day accounting operations, month-end-close processes, reconciliations, tax compliance, and financial planning and analysis. In my recent role as Controller at Lincoln Holdco, I managed the day-to-day accounting operation, optimized cash flow by building projections and led an audit. At the Center for Human Development, I implemented ASC 842 for hundreds of leases, led the migration of fixed assets and optimization of the A/P process. As the founder of Evergreen Ventures, I built systems and processes for locating distressed property owners and developed marketing strategies. Beyond my technical expertise, I am an effective leader and mentor, fostering growth and development within my teams. I have a proven track record of overseeing staff and ensuring deadlines are met, while maintaining a strong focus on communication and collaboration. I'm always eager to learn, innovate, and tackle new challenges. If you're looking for someone who can seamlessly navigate financial reporting complexities, implement cutting-edge solutions, and drive operational excellence, let's connect!

about: I am a CPA in the state of IL with a technical background. Most of my time is spent with financial statements and the care and maintenance of the systems that produce them. I have experience with the various QuickBooks flavors of course but I have used others, as I run across them. Moving from client to client requires the ability to adapt to whatever environment you are working in. My database administration background helps me get an intuitive picture of how the management system is structured and operates (or not operating). I also engage in process improvement and documentation. When I am called in it’s as backfill for someone who is leaving. Often, the company realizes they didn’t have a clear definition of what the former employee did, and now they’re in a bind. I correct that. And if they have an interest in improvement along the way, so much the better.

I'm still a strong believer in the Open-Source ethic, and still give my OwnYourOS talks to anyone who is willing to let me bend their ear.

recommendations: ["Dean Marucci “Navigating a career change can be an intimidating journey and especially in the Tech space where recruiters often hold a lot of industry insights and connections to that next role, it is so important to work with someone that you can trust. Like any fast-paced industry, recruiters can definitely be seen as cutthroat and it's easy to feel like another number in the mix of candidate pools. It is completely different with Jesse in the best possible ways. He is genuinely interested in trying to help YOU through that process to really make the right match that will allow you to thrive. He has such a good natured, calming presence about him and if there is a way that he can help, you can bet he will be the first to offer up any guidance, coaching, insights, or motivating words. Of all the recruiters I've worked with and met, Jesse was immediately the one that stood out and I personally have always been a bit skeptical because of the reputation recruiters often have. Feeling like I was chatting with a friend who really cared about helping me through this process was so valuable and completely energized me in my job hunt! I would recommend him to anyone who is in this process and looking for someone completely authentic with a desire to help.”","Joseph Johnson “I can not recommend Jesse enough. His thoroughness and professionalism was amazing. He helped me work through some resume issues and made sure I had an opportunity for interviews. Working with Jesse I was able to secure an amazing job that allowed me to move my family to be closer to family and friends post Covid lockdowns!”"]

about: I was very fortunate with my first job in IT. Working at PerceptIS has given me a lot of valuable experience. Much of that has to be credited to working with some wonderful and very bright people. My first assignment was working on campus at Case Western Reserve University (CWRU). It was great working with people that were extremely knowledgeable about so many different facets of the IT field. I gained a solid understanding of troubleshooting different issues. This involved working with Windows and Macintosh machines as well as mobile devices and printers. I then moved to supporting the University of Virginia as a Tier I Help Desk consultant. One of the great things about working with higher education is the variety of issues. Things are not standardized as is common in a typical business settings. UVa utilized Exchange, Google Apps, and another email system. That exposes a person to all three which they may not get in many other places. I believe that this variety is what makes me a great asset when it comes to troubleshooting client issues. I do everything I can to solve a caller's issue during the initial contact. There are issues that do require escalation. However, I am able to resolve the majority of calls received without further assistance. Most recently, I worked at the Sherwin-Williams Global Service Desk as an employee of Exodus Integrity Systems. I was initially brought in to help with migrating employees to Office 365. Fortunately, I was kept on and provided support to employees for problems relating to PC, iOS devices, and Sherwin-specific programs/apps. Having been in various IT support roles throughout the last 14 years I realize the importance of great customer service. A person should NEVER feel reticent to contact their technology support team/department. A great attitude and calm demeanor can go a long way.

about: Business Analyst Professional that enjoys creating business strategies based on Data Analysis and Business knowledge within fast-paced environments. That is why when I was 18 years old I started my career as a Financial Analyst at one of the top Investment Banking companies in the world. There I implemented solutions and optimized processes by analyzing financial data and market trends using Microsoft Office with an advanced level of Excel and Bloomberg, as well as a deep understanding of customer needs. With a Masters's in International Business and Business Analytics, I was able to participate in several projects where I applied my analysis skills by leveraging other powerful tools for data analysis including SQL and Python, as well as Data Visualization tools like Tableau and CRM Systems. I’m well-versed in creating a detailed Business Analysis, outlining problems, opportunities, and solutions for businesses. Thanks to my interpersonal and consultative skills I have been able to contribute to businesses' success by achieving set goals and expectations. I’d love to hear from you. You’re invited to explore my work and contact me so we can discuss how we can do some great work together. about: My background is primarily in music education where I have worked as an instructor, administrator, manager, and program director. I am also currently studying computer science at City College San Francisco. I have taught over 15,000 hours of private and group lessons to working professionals in San Francisco's FiDi and SoMa districts and have performed professionally for over 20 years in a variety of styles including classical, jazz, baroque, mariachi, rock, blues, and many more. I am currently a student at CCSF where I am finishing up certificates in javascript and web application programming and will move on to working towards an associates degree in computer science. So far I have completed courses in html, css, javascript, python, sql, and many more. I am looking to switch careers from being a musician to becoming either a web developer or a software engineer and hope to find entry level jobs in those fields. Ideally, I would love to combine my love of music with my love of programming to help educate the next generation of musicians, coders, or hopefully both.

recommendations: ["Jeremy Mason “Catherine is a phenomenal recruiter. Without a doubt the best recruiter I have ever worked with (or even spoken to for that matter). For one, she is extremely detail oriented. Throughout the process she meticulously goes over all crucial details about the interviews, the role, and the company. I knew exactly what I was getting into each step of the way. Especially as she is very up front and honest about all expectations. Secondly, Catherine has great time management skills. When she didn’t know a detail, she always found the correct information and got back to me within a day. Despite working in different time zones, she is always quick to respond and adjusts meeting schedules seamlessly. Finally, whether providing interview tips or assisting with salary negotiations, Catherine always goes above and beyond to help throughout the interview process. I can highly recommend her for anyone looking to find their next dream job or to hire the right candidate.”","Keonnii Ashman “Hands down Catherine is the best recruiter I have ever worked with. From the start to finish any question I had ranging from how to leave my old position to hey can you assist with getting another colleague placed. She was there to help. So glad she was able to help me achieve my dream of work in the cyber security sector.Thanks Catherine you are the best!!!!! ”"]

about: Robert Half Marketing & Creative (formally The Creative Group), quickly places skilled digital, marketing, and creative talent within top companies on a freelance contract-to-hire, project or full-time basis. As the creative and design staffing division of Robert Half Talent Solutions, we offer flexible solutions to meet companies' project and full-time employment needs. We have continually matched the world's best brands with hundreds of our wonderful local candidates! We are also able to support your technology, accounting and finance, administrative, and legal staffing needs, whether on a project or full-time basis. For 20 years, Robert Half has been named to Fortune® magazine’s list of “Most Admired Companies" Currently recruiting and staffing for: Graphic Designers - Copywriters - Account Managers - UI/UX Designers -Project Managers - Marketing Managers/ Specialists - SEO/PPC/SEM Specialists/Managers - Art Directors- Traffic Coordinators - Production Artists - E-Commerce Managers - Merchandising Coordinators - Web Designers - Front End Developers - Creative Directors - Art Directors - Copyeditors/Proofreaders... And many more. Looking for new opportunities? Please reach out! kieran.poirier@roberthalf.com

about: I am a finance professional who enjoys driving businesses forward, creating metrics and operating procedures. I partner with operations to understand and drive growth and cost containment. As a former business owner I have overcome many of the same challenges businesses face on a daily basis, both operationally and financially. My expertise is in strategic and tactical financial planning, operations, and P&L management for healthcare, manufacturing and service organizations. I have proven ability to develop and lead high-performing, cross-functional teams, manage situational challenges during periods of both declining sales and rapid growth, and to oversee operations and P&L for budgets of $250,000,000. I have demonstrated my skill in developing and translating strategic models into specific strategies to improve gross revenue and EBITDA. Specialties: Budgeting Financial Analysis Modeling Financial Management Forecasting Operations Management P&L Responsibility Income Statement & Balance Sheet Mergers & Acquisitions Acquisition Identification Due Diligence Cost Reduction Month End Close GAAP KPI Identification/ Reporting Capital Planning Capital Expenditures Contract Negotiations Strategic Planning Technologies: Excel Power BI Crystal Reports Tableau EPIC Oracle PeopleSoft Peachtree QuickBooks

As the Military and Veterans Services Coordinator for Oakland Community College my goal is to help make a significant difference in the lives of our military and veteran students. We also wish to serve dependents of our veterans. Veteran Focused; Skilled in Leadership; Coaching; Strong Interpersonal Skills; Seasoned Public Speaker. * Results oriented, dynamic professional with a diverse background in Management & Operations, Sales & Account Management, Education & Training, Recruiting, and Public Speaking. * Action oriented with excellent decision making abilities. Enjoy new challenges with a commitment to exceeding goals and objectives. * Approach new strategies and assignments with a positive attitude. * Proficient in Microsoft Office. Masters Degree of Business Administration in Business. A military adventure was blended with my civilian career. As a proud U.S. Navy Officer I retired from the Navy Reserve as a Chief Warrant Officer (W2). The following positions of leadership were held as I worked my way from enlisted to commissioned officer: work center supervisor; career counselor; chief petty officer; training officer; and officer recruiter. As a United Way Citizens Review Committee member I enjoyed participating in the allocation process of caring for the needs of my community. My journey has been wonderful. As I continue along life's path I seek to help make a significant difference in the lives of others as they reach for their goals. Veteran focused, I am organized and dependable. I apply the skills of communication, leadership, and team building daily. My Navy core values come to work with me everyday: Honor, Courage, and Commitment.

about: Experienced Business Administrator with a background in mid-sized to large professional services firms. Expertise includes leadership responsibility for accounts payable / receivables, reporting, purchasing, and tracking of capital assets / equipment, as well as, contract negotiations. Proficient with Microsoft Office, ERP Systems, Thomson Reuters - ACS, and QuickBooks. Accurate and organized with strong problem solving skills, strong attention to detail and the ability to communicate effectively with clients and staff at all levels. Customer-oriented professional; able to learn quickly and adapt well to changing environments. Leadership roles managing budgets & generating treasurer reports. Coordinating business plans using SWOT analysis, helping to raise over $100k through fundraising while chairing several committees. Reviewed vendor receipts and purchase orders to identify cost savings opportunities. Saved company approximately 10% on office supply commodities via proactive negotiations. Identified company assets & equipment located at hundreds of job sites nationwide. Collaborated with technical personnel to design reports that efficiently displayed inventory locations; enabled quick location of items for repair, streamlined ability to load software, and recall hardware assets from individuals no longer on staff. Responsible for accounts payable department audit which established that department procedures were 100% compliant annually.

Known for being a results-oriented individual, a quick learner, friendly and personable, and a self-starter with a willingness to work well as an individual contributor or member of a team. Summary of Strengths  Customer Relationship Management – Excellent at individualized relationships with customers with a proven track record of improving customer satisfaction and maximizing profits by providing the highest level of service. -Excellence Award Winner in 2005 for leading the Center’s E- Talk Scores which resulted in the highest customer satisfaction scores out of 4 call centers.  Account Sales Management – Experienced in being the point of contact, providing customer support, upselling, technical assistance, and relationship management. about: I'M HIRING! Send resumes to jason.obiedzinski@roberthalf.com The ideal candidate is a high-energy, sales-minded individual who thrives in a fast-paced and competitive environment. As a Recruiter, you will experience unlimited earning potential, a competitive base salary and a gratifying commission structure. As a Recruiter, your responsibilities will include: • Identify qualified candidates through a number of creative outlets (i.e. job boards, networking groups, social media, etc.). • Screen and assess candidates through phone screening, interviewing, skills testing, drug/background screening and conducting reference checks. • Managing the maintenance of current contractors on staff by ensuring excellent attendance, resolving any issues that arise and ensuring employee and client satisfaction. • Obtain and generate leads and set new meetings with prospective clients. • Assist with the management of client accounts by attending/shadowing meetings, sending correspondence and/or communicating with clients and resolving any issues. • Consistently meet and exceed weekly and quarterly quotas (To be established by Management Team upon employment).

about: I am a Branch Manager of Robert Half, the world’s first and largest specialized staffing firm, and a recognized leader in professional staffing and consulting services. In this role, I oversee the following divisions: Accountemps, OfficeTeam, and Salaried Professional Services specializing in the placement of temporary, temporary to full-time and consulting of accounting and finance professionals and, respectively; and OfficeTeam, specializing in the placement of highly skilled temporary administrative support. My focus is on quality customer service to both candidates and clients as well as being a member of my team. Robert Half has earned many accolades such as being named again to the World’s Most Admired Companies list by FORTUNE® magazine (March 18, 2013), ranking number one in the temporary help industry. Robert Half was named to Ethisphere’s “2013 World’s Most Ethical Companies” list. If you are interested in learning more about our company and services, please contact me. If you have an interest in the staffing industry as a profession, I would be excited to tell you more about why the staffing industry is predicted to be one of the fastest growing industries through 2018.

about: Over 7 years of professional recruiting experience consistent of full desk recruiting, client services, and leading staffing teams for fortune 100 companies. As an agency recruiter I thrived in fast paced, competitive environments while ensuring exceptional client and quality candidate experiences. My previous management experience confirmed my passion for building interpersonal relationships, people development, and leading teams. As a corporate recruiter I excelled at building internal processes and cross-organizational collaboration.
